{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"lexicalContext","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": [","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11SwiftSyntax0B0V","text":"Syntax","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"] { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Lexical contexts will have many of their details stripped out to prevent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macros from having visibility into unrelated code. For example, functions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and closures have their bodies removed, types and extensions have their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"member lists emptied, and properties and subscripts have their accessor","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"blocks removed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The first entry in the array is the innermost context. For attached","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macros, this is often the declaration to which the macro is attached.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This array can be empty if there is no context, for example when a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"freestanding macro is used at file scope.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"deprecationSummary":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"`MacroExpansionContext` conformance must implement `lexicalContext`","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.swift-syntax-macros\/documentation\/SwiftSyntaxMacros","doc:\/\/com.apple.swift-syntax-macros\/documentation\/SwiftSyntaxMacros\/MacroExpansionContext"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Return an array of enclosing lexical contexts for the purpose of macros,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"starting from the syntax node at which the macro expansion occurs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and containing all “context” nodes including functions, closures, types,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"properties, subscripts, and extensions."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftsyntaxmacros\/macroexpansioncontext\/lexicalcontext-478jr"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftSyntaxMacros"}],"title":"lexicalContext","platforms":[{"beta":false,"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","deprecated":false}],"externalID":"s:17SwiftSyntaxMacros21MacroExpansionContextPAAE07lexicalF0Say0aB00B0VGvp","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","extendedModule":"SwiftSyntaxMacros","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"lexicalContext"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11SwiftSyntax0B0V","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Syntax"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.swift-syntax-macros\/documentation\/SwiftSyntaxMacros\/MacroExpansionContext\/lexicalContext-478jr"},"references":{"doc://com.apple.swift-syntax-macros/documentation/SwiftSyntaxMacros/MacroExpansionContext/lexicalContext-478jr":{"deprecated":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.swift-syntax-macros\/documentation\/SwiftSyntaxMacros\/MacroExpansionContext\/lexicalContext-478jr","title":"lexicalContext","abstract":[{"text":"Return an array of enclosing lexical contexts for the purpose of macros,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"starting from the syntax node at which the macro expansion occurs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and containing 